footnotes.text: The Screening Visit must be performed within 28 days of randomization.
When an Investigator has determined that a subject should discontinue the study, a Final Visit will be conducted.
A Follow-Up visit is required if the Final Visit is < 30 days from the last administration of drug.

Following completion of platinum doublet therapy, maintenance pemetrexed 500 mg q3 weeks is strongly encouraged for all subjects who are suitable candidates. For those subjects in maintenance therapy, tumor assessments will be completed q9 weeks until radiographic progression.
Physical exam not required, if performed within 7 days prior to randomization. Height is only measured at Screening.
May occur up to 4 calendar days before C1D-2 to facilitate dispensing and morning administration of Study Drug.

Serum pregnancy test will be done at Screening. Urine pregnancy test will be done prior to dosing at C1D-2 unless the serum pregnancy test was collected within 7 days of C1D-2. Local urine pregnancy testing should also be performed at each subsequent Cycle Day 1 visit.

Study samples for central laboratory analysis may be performed within 72 hours of the scheduled day. A qualified local laboratory may be used to perform laboratory analyses for treatment decisions but this cannot replace the central laboratory analysis on a protocol defined visit.

Baseline tumor assessments must be conducted within 28 days (inclusive) of randomization. Post-baseline tumor assessment will be conducted within 7 days prior to chemotherapy on C3D1 and C5D1, every 9 weeks ± 7 days from the last scan after treatment discontinuation until 1 year on study, and then every 12 weeks ± 7 days.
Following treatment discontinuation, subjects will have post-treatment visits q9 weeks until one year after randomization, then q12 weeks until radiographic progression or death.
